1527766196845563905.title: One of California's richest enclaves is uninsurable against wildfires
1527766196845563905.description:
Montecito is one of the world’s wealthiest enclaves. 

The exclusive Central Coast town, on the southern tip of Santa Barbara County, has just 8,200 people living in 9.2 square miles on the coast of the Pacific Ocean. 

It also happens to occupy one of the most dangerous and increasingly active climate change-fueled disaster footprints in the U.S.

To live there not only means paying a premium — but risking it all.
